<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,152,1454]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">
This species is morphologically closest to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" authorityYear="1799" box="[694,1008,1196,1221]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="corymbosum">
<emphasis box="[694,1008,1196,1221]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Heliotropium corymbosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one of the most widespread species of the group. However, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" authorityYear="1799" box="[457,656,1235,1260]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="corymbosum">
<emphasis box="[457,656,1235,1260]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">H. corymbosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a species of at least seasonally dry habitats. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Luebert &amp; Weigend" authorityYear="2012" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oxapampanum">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">Heliotropium oxapampanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" authorityYear="1799" box="[534,720,1273,1298]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="corymbosum">
<emphasis box="[534,720,1273,1298]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">H. corymbosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by a style shorter than or equal to the stigmatic head (versus style longer than the stigmatic head in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" authorityYear="1799" box="[605,790,1312,1337]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="corymbosum">
<emphasis box="[605,790,1312,1337]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">H. corymbosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and sepals hirsute and acute (versus strigose and long acuminate in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ruiz &amp; Pavon" authorityYear="1799" box="[308,493,1351,1376]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="corymbosum">
<emphasis box="[308,493,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">H. corymbosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Luebert, F. &amp; Weigend, M. &amp; Hilger, H. H." box="[566,793,1350,1376]" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" pagination="1263 - 1266" refId="ref5110" refString="Luebert, F., Weigend, M. &amp; Hilger, H. H. (2010). Epitypification of Heliotropium arborescens L. (Heliotropiaceae). Taxon 59: 1263 - 1266." type="journal article" year="2010">
Luebert 
<emphasis box="[664,723,1351,1376]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="43">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). It also resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Johnston (1928: 43)" authorityName="Johnston" authorityPageNumber="43" authorityYear="1928" box="[1017,1405,1350,1376]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Heliotropium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Boraginales" pageId="8" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mandonii">
